meta.description: Pet breed database with zodiac compatibility for freshblogs.cc/pets

breeds.name: Labrador Retriever
breeds.description: America's most popular dog breed for good reason. Labs are endlessly enthusiastic, loving, and adaptable companions who thrive in active families.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise and mental stimulation. Prone to weight gain; monitor diet closely. Loves water and retrieving games.

breeds.name: Golden Retriever
breeds.description: The ultimate family dog. Golden Retrievers combine intelligence with an almost supernatural patience and gentleness that makes them beloved worldwide.
breeds.care_notes: Daily exercise essential. Regular brushing 2-3x per week. Prone to hip dysplasia; maintain healthy weight.

breeds.name: French Bulldog
breeds.description: The Frenchie is city living perfected. Compact, charming, and hilariously expressive, they thrive in apartments and adore their humans.
breeds.care_notes: Cannot tolerate heat or strenuous exercise. Clean facial wrinkles weekly. Brachycephalic — avoid extreme temperatures.

breeds.name: German Shepherd
breeds.description: The gold standard of working dogs. German Shepherds combine exceptional intelligence with unwavering loyalty and a natural protective instinct.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours of daily exercise and mental challenges. Sheds heavily twice a year. Benefits from early socialization.

breeds.name: Bulldog
breeds.description: Don't let the grumpy face fool you — Bulldogs are among the sweetest, most docile breeds. They're perfectly happy with minimal exercise and maximum cuddles.
breeds.care_notes: Cannot tolerate heat. Clean wrinkles and tail pocket regularly. Prone to respiratory issues; avoid overexertion.

breeds.name: Poodle (Standard)
breeds.description: Don't let the haircut fool you — Standard Poodles are among the most intelligent, athletic, and versatile dogs in existence.
breeds.care_notes: Daily exercise required. Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks. Excels at dog sports, therapy work, and learning new tricks.

breeds.name: Beagle
breeds.description: Beagles follow their nose everywhere — which means they need a secure yard and leash at all times. Their happiness is utterly contagious.
breeds.care_notes: Needs secure fencing — they follow their nose! High prey drive. Regular ear cleaning to prevent infections.

breeds.name: Rottweiler
breeds.description: Beneath the intimidating exterior is a devoted family dog with a silly streak. Rottweilers are deeply loyal and surprisingly gentle with their families.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization and training critical. Needs daily exercise. Not recommended for first-time owners. Thrives with a job to do.

breeds.name: Yorkshire Terrier
breeds.description: What Yorkies lack in size they more than make up for in personality. These tiny dogs have enormous courage and an outsized sense of their own importance.
breeds.care_notes: Daily hair brushing if kept long. Prone to dental issues; regular brushing essential. Can be snappy with small children.

breeds.name: Dachshund
breeds.description: Built like a sausage and stubborn as a mule, Dachshunds are nonetheless deeply devoted to their families and surprisingly brave hunters.
breeds.care_notes: Protect from jumping to prevent back injuries (IVDD). Two coat varieties need different grooming. Can be stubborn in training.

breeds.name: Siberian Husky
breeds.description: Part sled dog, part escape artist, part comedian. Huskies are breathtaking, athletic, and require owners who truly understand high-energy independent breeds.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise — hours, not minutes. Escape artists; needs very secure fencing. Heavy shedding twice yearly.

breeds.name: Doberman Pinscher
breeds.description: Elegant, powerful, and intensely loyal. Dobermans are among the finest personal protection dogs and devoted family companions for experienced owners.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily mental and physical exercise. Early socialization essential. Sensitive to cold temperatures. Thrives with a job.

breeds.name: Australian Shepherd
breeds.description: Aussies are working dogs through and through — brilliant, tireless, and happiest when given a job. They are not ideal for couch potato households.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours of vigorous daily exercise. Mental stimulation as important as physical. Excels at dog sports and herding.

breeds.name: Boxer
breeds.description: Boxers are perpetual puppies — playful, exuberant, and devoted family clowns who adore children and maintain their puppy energy well into adulthood.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily exercise. Brachycephalic — avoid heat. Early training recommended due to size and exuberance.

breeds.name: Cavalier King Charles Spaniel
breeds.description: The perfect lap dog that also loves adventure. Cavaliers adapt to any lifestyle and are among the sweetest, most adaptable companion dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular ear and eye cleaning. Can develop heart conditions — regular vet checks essential. Moderate exercise needs.

breeds.name: Miniature Schnauzer
breeds.description: Miniature Schnauzers are big dogs in small packages — alert, spirited, and fearlessly opinionated. They make excellent watchdogs and devoted companions.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming every 5-8 weeks. Prone to pancreatitis; monitor diet. Energetic — needs daily exercise.

breeds.name: Shih Tzu
breeds.description: Shih Tzus were bred to be the companions of emperors, and they've never forgotten it. These charming, adaptable dogs thrive in any home that gives them love.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing if coat kept long. Regular ear cleaning and teeth brushing. Low exercise needs — ideal for apartment life.

breeds.name: Great Dane
breeds.description: The gentle giant. Despite their imposing size, Great Danes are among the most patient, docile dogs — they just happen to take up the entire couch.
breeds.care_notes: Joint health critical — avoid overexertion in puppies. Bloat risk — divide meals. Shorter lifespan than smaller breeds.

breeds.name: Pomeranian
breeds.description: Pomeranians are tiny furballs with the personality of a much larger dog — bold, curious, and completely convinced of their own magnificence.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing. Can be yappy — early training helps. Despite energy, exercise needs are manageable for their size.

breeds.name: Border Collie
breeds.description: Widely considered the most intelligent dog breed. Border Collies are working dogs who need a serious job or they will invent one — usually involving herding children.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours of vigorous mental and physical exercise daily. Not suitable for casual owners. Thrives in dog sports.

breeds.name: Maltese
breeds.description: Ancient, elegant, and surprisingly feisty. Maltese have been prized companions for millennia and their timeless beauty and devotion endure.
breeds.care_notes: Daily coat brushing. Prone to dental issues — regular brushing essential. Tear stain management needed.

breeds.name: Weimaraner
breeds.description: Weimaraners are called the Grey Ghost for their sleek, silvery coat and their tendency to shadow their owners everywhere. They need active households.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours of daily exercise. Prone to separation anxiety. Not suitable for apartment life. Strong hunting instinct.

breeds.name: Pug
breeds.description: Pugs are little philosophers — content to observe life from the comfort of a soft cushion. Their expressive faces and comedy timing are legendary.
breeds.care_notes: Clean facial wrinkles regularly. Brachycephalic — avoid heat and overexertion. Prone to obesity; monitor diet.

breeds.name: Cocker Spaniel
breeds.description: Merry, gentle, and endlessly sweet. Cocker Spaniels are the eternal optimists of the dog world, greeting each day with their signature happy ears bouncing.
breeds.care_notes: Regular ear cleaning to prevent infections. Grooming every 6-8 weeks. Moderate daily exercise. Can be sensitive.

breeds.name: Bernese Mountain Dog
breeds.description: Gentle giants from the Swiss Alps. Berners are tricolor beauties with warm, patient temperaments and deep devotion to their families.
breeds.care_notes: Prone to joint issues and cancer. Regular brushing. Shorter lifespan — make every year count. Moderate exercise needs.

breeds.name: Poodle (Miniature)
breeds.description: All the intelligence and elegance of the Standard Poodle in a more apartment-friendly size. Miniature Poodles are versatile, loving, and clever.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks. Daily exercise needed. Excels at agility and obedience. Highly trainable.

breeds.name: Shetland Sheepdog
breeds.description: Shelties are miniature working dogs with big hearts. They're vocal, intelligent, and deeply devoted — perfect for active families who love a beautiful fluffy companion.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing. Sensitive to harsh treatment. Barking can be managed with training. Excels at agility.

breeds.name: Chihuahua
breeds.description: The world's smallest breed with the world's largest attitude. Chihuahuas are fierce little personalities who bond intensely with their chosen human.
breeds.care_notes: Can be fragile — supervise with children and larger dogs. Dental issues common. Can become overly possessive; socialize early.

breeds.name: Pembroke Welsh Corgi
breeds.description: Royal dogs with a herding heritage and surprisingly athletic bodies hidden under adorable fluffiness. Corgis are intelligent, loyal, and endlessly entertaining.
breeds.care_notes: Daily exercise — more than their size suggests. Prone to weight gain. Regular brushing. Can be vocal.

breeds.name: Bloodhound
breeds.description: The world's finest nose on the world's most good-natured dog. Bloodhounds are gentle giants who follow their noses with a tenacity that requires secure leashing.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily exercise but not intense. Long ears need regular cleaning. Drooling is significant. Follows scents relentlessly.

breeds.name: Irish Setter
breeds.description: Gorgeous mahogany dogs with the energy of a rocket and the sweetness of a saint. Irish Setters are perpetually enthusiastic and take longer than most to mature.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise — hours of running. Regular brushing. Long maturation period. Wonderful with an active family.

breeds.name: Akita
breeds.description: Sacred in Japan, the Akita is a powerful, dignified breed of profound loyalty. They bond intensely with family and are not recommended for first-time owners.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization critical. Not dog-park friendly. Needs experienced owner. Deeply loyal but independent.

breeds.name: Boston Terrier
breeds.description: The American Gentleman — tuxedo coat, impeccable manners, and genuine urban adaptability. Boston Terriers are wonderful city dogs who love everyone.
breeds.care_notes: Brachycephalic — avoid heat. Clean facial wrinkles. Moderate exercise needs. Very adaptable.

breeds.name: Havanese
breeds.description: Cuba's national dog and one of the happiest little companions you'll find. Havanese are adaptable, non-shedding, and deeply social.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing or professional grooming. Non-shedding — great for allergy sufferers. Needs companionship — dislikes being alone.

breeds.name: Saint Bernard
breeds.description: The iconic rescue dog of the Alps. Saint Bernards are enormous, patient, and remarkably gentle — especially with children — despite their imposing size.
breeds.care_notes: Prone to bloat and hip dysplasia. Regular brushing. Significant drooling. Moderate exercise — not a running companion.

breeds.name: Vizsla
breeds.description: The Velcro dog — Vizslas attach themselves to their owners with a devotion that is both touching and occasionally suffocating. Athletic, gentle, and brilliant.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours of vigorous exercise daily. Prone to separation anxiety. Excels at running, hunting, and dog sports.

breeds.name: Bichon Frisé
breeds.description: A cloud of white fluffiness with a perpetually sunny disposition. Bichons are hypoallergenic, non-shedding, and relentlessly cheerful companions.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming every 4-6 weeks. Non-shedding — good for allergy sufferers. Needs daily exercise and companionship.

breeds.name: Dalmatian
breeds.description: The iconic spotted dog needs serious exercise and an experienced owner. Dalmatians are athletic, intelligent, and can be challenging for novices.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive daily exercise. Some are deaf — test puppies. Originally carriage dogs; need a 'job'. Can be intense.

breeds.name: Newfoundland
breeds.description: Gentle giants bred for water rescue. Newfoundlands are among the sweetest, most patient dogs in existence — natural nannies for children.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing and grooming. Significant drooling and shedding. Prone to bloat. Needs moderate exercise and access to water.

breeds.name: Jack Russell Terrier
breeds.description: Maximum dog in minimum package. Jack Russells are tireless, fearless hunters who need experienced owners who can match their extraordinary energy.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive daily exercise — hours, not a short walk. High prey drive. Can be dog-aggressive. Not for novice owners.

breeds.name: Whippet
breeds.description: Greyhounds in apartment-friendly sizes. Whippets sprint at 35mph but are surprisingly calm indoors — the perfect combination of athlete and lap dog.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily runs or free running in a secure area. Very sensitive to cold. Minimal grooming. Excellent apartment dogs.

breeds.name: Boxer-Labrador Mix
breeds.description: The best of both breeds — the Labrador's friendliness with the Boxer's playfulness. Boxadors are wonderful family dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Daily vigorous exercise. Moderate grooming. Benefits from early training due to size and energy.

breeds.name: Shiba Inu
breeds.description: Japan's most popular native breed — the Shiba is fox-like in appearance and cat-like in independence. Spirited, loyal, and famously dramatic.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization essential. High prey drive. Escape artists. The Shiba scream is real. Needs patient, experienced owner.

breeds.name: Greyhound
breeds.description: Despite being the world's fastest dog, Greyhounds are remarkably calm couch potatoes at home. They are gentle, elegant, and surprisingly low-maintenance.
breeds.care_notes: Daily sprint in a secure area needed. Sensitive to cold. Very low grooming needs. Makes an excellent apartment dog.

breeds.name: Basenji
breeds.description: The barkless dog from Central Africa. Basenjis are cat-like in independence and cleanliness, making unique yodeling sounds instead of traditional barks.
breeds.care_notes: High prey drive — must be leashed. Extremely difficult to recall. Independent thinkers. Not for inexperienced owners.

breeds.name: Norwegian Elkhound
breeds.description: Ancient hunting dogs from Scandinavia. Norwegian Elkhounds are hardy, independent, and deeply loyal — a beautiful silver companion with a bold spirit.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise. Heavy shedder. Independent streak makes early training important.

breeds.name: Leonberger
breeds.description: Resembling a lion, the Leonberger is a gentle giant with magnificent presence. Bred as a companion to royalty, they remain noble, patient family dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Prone to joint issues and heart conditions. Shorter lifespan. Needs moderate daily exercise.

breeds.name: Keeshond
breeds.description: Dutch barge dogs with spectacular double coats and spectacled faces. Keeshonds are sociable, alert companions who thrive in family environments.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing — heavy seasonal shedding. Alert watchdogs without being aggressive. Excellent family dog.

breeds.name: Chesapeake Bay Retriever
breeds.description: America's water retriever. Chesapeakes are tough, determined working dogs with a more independent personality than other retrievers.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise, especially swimming. More independent than Labradors. Needs experienced owner.

breeds.name: Affenpinscher
breeds.description: The Monkey Terrier. Affenpinschers have ridiculous faces and matching personalities — hilariously stubborn, mischievous, and entertaining.
breeds.care_notes: Moderate exercise needs. Consistent training required due to stubbornness. Good watchdog despite small size.

breeds.name: Plott Hound
breeds.description: North Carolina's state dog. Plott Hounds are tenacious hunting dogs with incredible endurance and loyalty to their family pack.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive daily exercise. High prey drive. Vocalization can be intense. Best for active outdoor families.

breeds.name: Basenji-Greyhound Mix
breeds.description: An athletic mix combining Greyhound's grace with Basenji's independence. Unique, low-maintenance companions for experienced owners.
breeds.care_notes: High prey drive. Needs daily running. Relatively independent. Minimal grooming.

breeds.name: Papillon
breeds.description: Named for their butterfly-shaped ears. Papillons are tiny athletes with vast intelligence — among the smartest small breeds, excelling at agility.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing. High energy for size — needs daily exercise. Excels at agility and obedience competition.

breeds.name: Saluki
breeds.description: One of the oldest breeds in existence. Salukis are elegant, aristocratic sighthounds who are deeply devoted to their families but aloof with strangers.
breeds.care_notes: Needs secure running space — incredibly fast. Independent and sometimes stubborn. Sensitive to harsh training.

breeds.name: Airedale Terrier
breeds.description: The King of Terriers. Airedales are the largest terrier breed — versatile working dogs with intelligence, courage, and a classic terrier stubbornness.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Stubborn — needs patient, consistent training. High energy needs. Strong prey drive.

breeds.name: Keeshond (Standard)
breeds.description: Dutch canal dogs known for their spectacular ring tail and 'spectacles' facial markings. Keeshonds are devoted, lively family companions.
breeds.care_notes: Heavy shedding seasons require extra brushing. Alert watchdogs. Excellent family dog. Needs daily walks.

breeds.name: Cane Corso
breeds.description: Ancient Italian mastiff with majestic presence. Cane Corsos are deeply devoted to family but require experienced ownership and early socialization.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization and professional training critical. Not for first-time owners. Needs moderate daily exercise.

breeds.name: Samoyed
breeds.description: The smiling sled dog. Samoyeds are breathtakingly beautiful white dogs with permanently smiling faces and genuinely sunny temperaments.
breeds.care_notes: Brushing 3-4x weekly to manage shedding. Needs vigorous daily exercise. Originally bred for cold — tolerates it well.

breeds.name: Bull Terrier
breeds.description: The egg-headed clown of the dog world. Bull Terriers are intensely playful, comically determined, and devoted to their families.
breeds.care_notes: High energy — needs vigorous exercise. Not always reliable with other dogs or small animals. Needs patient, firm training.

breeds.name: Alaskan Malamute
breeds.description: Working sled dogs at heart. Malamutes are powerful, independent, and playful — but they require experienced owners who understand pack dynamics.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise. Strong prey drive. Dog aggression possible. Heavy shedder. Not for first-time owners.

breeds.name: Soft Coated Wheaten Terrier
breeds.description: The terrier with a soft, silky wheaten coat and an irresistibly joyful personality. Wheatens are devoted, energetic companions who love to play.
breeds.care_notes: Regular professional grooming. High energy — needs daily vigorous exercise. Strong prey drive. Generally good with children.

breeds.name: Portuguese Water Dog
breeds.description: Non-shedding water dogs who became famous as the Obama family's choice. PWDs are athletic, intelligent, and wonderful family companions.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks. Needs vigorous daily exercise including swimming. Highly trainable.

breeds.name: Canaan Dog
breeds.description: Ancient herding and guard dogs from the Middle East. Canaan Dogs are naturally wary but deeply loyal to their families.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization critical. Independent thinkers. Alert watchdogs. Moderate exercise needs.

breeds.name: Tibetan Mastiff
breeds.description: Ancient guardian of Tibetan monasteries. Tibetan Mastiffs are powerful, independent, and deeply devoted to their family territory.
breeds.care_notes: Not for first-time owners. Strong will requires experienced handler. Heavy shedding seasons. Nocturnal tendencies.

breeds.name: Lagotto Romagnolo
breeds.description: The truffle dog of Italy. Lagottos are ancient water dogs repurposed as truffle hunters — intelligent, affectionate, and surprisingly hypoallergenic.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming needed. Loves to dig — redirect to sandpits. Needs mental stimulation and daily exercise.

breeds.name: Puli
breeds.description: The dreadlocked herding dog. Pulik have distinctive corded coats and lightning-fast agility — they're versatile, loyal herding dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Coat care is labor-intensive — cords must be separated regularly. High energy herding dog needs vigorous daily exercise.

breeds.name: Norwegian Lundehund
breeds.description: Six-toed puffin hunters from Norway's remote islands. Lundehunds are unique, acrobatic, and one of the rarest breeds in the world.
breeds.care_notes: Prone to intestinal protein-losing conditions. Special diet often needed. Rare breed — find specialist breeder.

breeds.name: Miniature Pinscher
breeds.description: The King of Toys — Min Pins are bold, fearless dogs who have no concept of their size. They are the terriers of the toy group.
breeds.care_notes: High energy despite small size. Needs daily exercise and mental stimulation. Early socialization essential.

breeds.name: Field Spaniel
breeds.description: Between the Cocker and Springer in size, the Field Spaniel is a gentle, sensitive, and versatile hunting companion.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Sensitive to harsh training. Moderate daily exercise. Less well-known than related spaniels.

breeds.name: Flat-Coated Retriever
breeds.description: Peter Pan in dog form. Flat-Coats maintain puppy enthusiasm well into adulthood — eternally optimistic, forever joyful.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise. Shorter lifespan — genetic predisposition to cancer. Exuberant and requires patient training.

breeds.name: Dogo Argentino
breeds.description: Powerful Argentine hunting dogs developed for big game. Dogos are deeply loyal to family but require experienced ownership and early socialization.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization and training essential. Not suitable for multi-pet homes due to prey drive. Needs experienced owner.

breeds.name: Otterhound
breeds.description: One of the rarest breeds in the world. Otterhounds are exuberant, shaggy, and wonderfully friendly — great family dogs for active households.
breeds.care_notes: Needs vigorous daily exercise including swimming. Shaggy coat needs regular brushing. Rare breed — difficult to find.

breeds.name: Sussex Spaniel
breeds.description: Among the most laid-back spaniels. Sussex Spaniels combine a calm temperament with genuine cheerfulness and moderate exercise needs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Moderate exercise needs. Rare breed. Excellent for less active families who still want a sporty dog.

breeds.name: Standard Schnauzer
breeds.description: The original Schnauzer — working farm dogs with intelligence, reliability, and a square-jawed dignity. The foundation for both the Miniature and Giant varieties.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming every 6-8 weeks. High energy — needs daily vigorous exercise. Strong-willed but trainable.

breeds.name: Boykin Spaniel
breeds.description: South Carolina's state dog. Boykins are versatile, eager-to-please hunting companions who also make wonderful family dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. High energy — needs vigorous daily exercise. Excels as both hunting dog and family companion.

breeds.name: Black and Tan Coonhound
breeds.description: All-American hunting dogs with incredible noses and melodious voices. Coonhounds are gentle, friendly giants who love to vocalize.
breeds.care_notes: Needs secure fencing — will follow nose anywhere. Vocal — may not suit apartments. Needs daily exercise.

breeds.name: Giant Schnauzer
breeds.description: The Giant Schnauzer is a serious working dog — powerful, dominant, and deeply loyal. They require experienced owners who can provide structure and leadership.
breeds.care_notes: Experienced owner required. Needs vigorous daily exercise and mental stimulation. Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks.

breeds.name: Rhodesian Ridgeback
breeds.description: Bred to hunt lions. Ridgebacks are powerful, independent, and deeply loyal — with a distinctive ridge of reversed hair along their spine.
breeds.care_notes: Early socialization critical. Independent — not ideal for first-time owners. Needs vigorous daily exercise.

breeds.name: English Springer Spaniel
breeds.description: The merry springer — boundless enthusiasm, genuine affection, and impressive sporting ability. Springers are among the finest family-friendly gun dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming and ear cleaning. High energy — needs vigorous daily exercise. Excellent with children.

breeds.name: Miniature Bull Terrier
breeds.description: All the Bull Terrier personality in a smaller, equally hilarious package. Mini Bull Terriers are endlessly entertaining and deeply devoted.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily vigorous exercise. Strong-willed. Not always good with other dogs. Needs patient, consistent training.

breeds.name: Xoloitzcuintli
breeds.description: One of the world's oldest and rarest breeds. The Mexican Hairless Dog was sacred to the Aztecs and remains a unique, devoted companion.
breeds.care_notes: Sunscreen needed if in sun. Skin care required. Moderate exercise. Rare — find reputable breeder.

breeds.name: Briard
breeds.description: Heart wrapped in fur — the Briard is a large French herding breed of remarkable intelligence and fierce devotion to its family.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Needs vigorous daily exercise. Can be reserved with strangers. Early socialization important.

breeds.name: Norwegian Buhund
breeds.description: Viking-era herding dogs who sailed with Norsemen. Norwegian Buhunds are alert, lively, and form deep bonds with their families.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing. High energy — needs daily vigorous exercise. Alert watchdog. Excellent herding instincts.

breeds.name: Ibizan Hound
breeds.description: Ancient dogs from the Balearic Islands — lean, elegant, and athletic sighthounds who are playful at home and magnificent runners.
breeds.care_notes: Needs secure fencing — exceptional jumpers. Needs daily running. Sensitive to cold. Independent thinkers.

breeds.name: American Eskimo Dog
breeds.description: Beautiful white cloud dogs with sharp intelligence and an eagerness to please. American Eskimos excel at tricks and agility.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing for thick double coat. High energy — needs daily exercise. Can be vocal. Excellent trick dogs.

breeds.name: Belgian Malinois
breeds.description: The world's premier working dog. Belgian Malinois are used by military and police worldwide — extraordinary intelligence with boundless work drive.
breeds.care_notes: Not suitable for novice owners. Needs hours of daily mental and physical exercise. Needs a job. Extremely high drive.

breeds.name: Irish Wolfhound
breeds.description: The tallest dog breed. Irish Wolfhounds are gentle, patient giants with genuine kindness and a quiet dignity that belies their ancient hunting heritage.
breeds.care_notes: Shorter lifespan typical of giant breeds. Moderate exercise needs. Joint supplements recommended. Gentle indoor companion.

breeds.name: Treeing Walker Coonhound
breeds.description: Bred to tree raccoons with relentless drive. Treeing Walkers are energetic, vocal hounds who need active outdoor families.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive daily exercise. Vocal — not ideal for apartments. Strong prey drive. Secure fencing essential.

breeds.name: Tibetan Spaniel
breeds.description: Ancient Buddhist monastery dogs. Tibetan Spaniels are independent, intelligent, and somewhat cat-like in their selective affection.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Independent but devoted to family. Good watchdog. Moderate exercise needs.

breeds.name: Plott Hound (American)
breeds.description: North Carolina's state dog. Plott Hounds are determined, energetic hunting dogs with deep loyalty to their pack.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive daily exercise. Vocal baying. High prey drive. Best for active outdoor enthusiasts.

breeds.name: Schipperke
breeds.description: The little black fox. Schipperkes are curious, mischievous boat dogs with boundless energy and an entertaining personality.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing. High energy — needs daily exercise. Independent and sometimes stubborn. Alert watchdog.

breeds.name: Persian
breeds.description: The royalty of the cat world. Persians are placid, elegant, and deeply devoted to their humans — preferring a quiet indoor life of luxury.
breeds.care_notes: Daily grooming essential — mats form easily. Clean facial wrinkles. Prone to respiratory and kidney issues.

breeds.name: Maine Coon
breeds.description: The gentle giant of cat breeds. Maine Coons are huge, tufted, dog-like cats who enjoy water, fetch, and following their humans everywhere.
breeds.care_notes: Twice-weekly brushing. Prone to heart disease (HCM) — screen regularly. Loves water and interactive play.

breeds.name: Siamese
breeds.description: The extroverts of the cat world. Siamese are strikingly beautiful, extraordinarily vocal, and require significant social engagement.
breeds.care_notes: Regular interaction essential — can develop separation anxiety. Vocal — neighbors should be warned. Highly intelligent.

breeds.name: Ragdoll
breeds.description: Named for their tendency to go limp when held. Ragdolls are incredibly gentle, calm, and ideal for families seeking a supremely relaxed companion.
breeds.care_notes: Semi-long coat needs twice-weekly brushing. Prone to HCM — cardiac screening important. Very trusting — keep indoors.

breeds.name: Bengal
breeds.description: Part domestic cat, part small wild leopard. Bengals are athletic, mischievous, and need serious environmental enrichment to stay out of trouble.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive playtime and vertical space. Can open cabinets and doors. High prey drive. Not for low-energy households.

breeds.name: Abyssinian
breeds.description: One of the oldest known cat breeds. Abyssinians are slender, athletic, and endlessly curious — they need constant entertainment.
breeds.care_notes: Needs significant environmental enrichment and playtime. Very active — not a lap cat. Interactive toys essential.

breeds.name: Scottish Fold
breeds.description: Those folded ears are adorable, but ethical breeding is important. Scottish Folds are calm, sweet cats who adapt beautifully to family life.
breeds.care_notes: Folded ears from genetic mutation — only breed from straight-eared cats to avoid joint issues. Regular ear cleaning needed.

breeds.name: Sphynx
breeds.description: The hairless wonder. Sphynx cats are incredibly warm to the touch, intensely social, and completely without the dignity most cats maintain.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly skin bathing to remove oil buildup. Prone to cold. Needs regular ear cleaning. Heart conditions possible.

breeds.name: British Shorthair
breeds.description: The teddy bear cat. British Shorthairs are round, plush, and wonderfully self-contained — loving but not demanding, playful but never frenetic.
breeds.care_notes: Prone to obesity — monitor diet. Blood group B is common — check before breeding. Easy care coat.

breeds.name: Russian Blue
breeds.description: Silver-blue cats with emerald eyes and a shy, gentle nature. Russian Blues are loyal to their family but cautious with strangers.
breeds.care_notes: Prone to obesity — monitor diet. Shy initially — allow time to warm up. Very clean and quiet cats.

breeds.name: Norwegian Forest Cat
breeds.description: Nordic forest hunters with magnificent waterproof coats. Wegies are sturdy, independent, and genuinely beautiful cats who enjoy outdoor exploration.
breeds.care_notes: Twice-weekly brushing. Needs vertical climbing space. Semi-independent — enjoys outdoor access if possible.

breeds.name: Birman
breeds.description: Sacred cats of Burma. Birmans are strikingly beautiful with their colorpoint patterns and pure white gloves — gentle and deeply devoted.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing for silky coat. Sociable — does well with other pets. Gentle and non-demanding.

breeds.name: Tonkinese
breeds.description: A Siamese-Burmese cross that captures the best of both breeds — playful, social, and affectionate without Siamese extremes.
breeds.care_notes: Needs regular interaction and play. Can be vocal but less extreme than Siamese. Prone to dental issues.

breeds.name: Turkish Angora
breeds.description: One of the oldest natural breeds. Turkish Angoras are graceful, intelligent, and often mischievously entertaining — they choose one person as their special person.
breeds.care_notes: Minimal grooming despite long coat. Bonds deeply with one person. Active and athletic — needs playtime.

breeds.name: Burmese
breeds.description: People-oriented to an extreme degree. Burmese are the social butterflies of the cat world — loving, vocal, and genuinely sad when left alone.
breeds.care_notes: Needs significant social time — gets lonely easily. Very long-lived. Vocal but not as extreme as Siamese.

breeds.name: Himalayan
breeds.description: Persian-Siamese cross with colorpoint markings. Himalayans are calm, gentle, and beautiful indoor companions.
breeds.care_notes: Daily grooming essential. Clean facial wrinkles. Prone to kidney disease. Quiet, calm indoor cats.

breeds.name: Devon Rex
breeds.description: Pixie-faced, huge-eared, and endlessly mischievous. Devon Rex cats are people-oriented, athletic, and warm — living hot water bottles who follow you everywhere.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly ear cleaning. Minimal shedding. Needs warmth. Very social — suffers without companionship.

breeds.name: Cornish Rex
breeds.description: Soft-coated cats with waves in their fur and extraordinary athleticism. Cornish Rex are perpetually kitten-like in their energy.
breeds.care_notes: Minimal shedding. Needs warmth. Very social and active. Excels at fetch and agility.

breeds.name: Exotic Shorthair
breeds.description: The lazy man's Persian — all the beauty and temperament with less grooming. Exotics are placid, charming, and wonderfully easy cats.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly brushing. Clean facial wrinkles regularly. Prone to same conditions as Persians.

breeds.name: American Shorthair
breeds.description: The all-American cat — adaptable, healthy, and excellent hunters. American Shorthairs are wonderful family cats with moderate needs.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Healthy, long-lived breed. Moderate exercise and play needs. Good with children and dogs.

breeds.name: Savannah
breeds.description: Part serval, part domestic cat. Savannahs are the largest domestic cat breed — athletic, curious, and absolutely stunning.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive space and enrichment. Leash-trainable. Early generation cats require special permits. Very high energy.

breeds.name: Chartreux
breeds.description: Ancient French cats with blue coats and copper eyes. Chartreux are quiet, observant, and deeply devoted without being demanding.
breeds.care_notes: Minimal grooming. Very quiet — rarely vocalizes. Devoted companion. Healthy robust breed.

breeds.name: Balinese
breeds.description: Siamese with long silky coats and a slightly softer personality. Balinese are social, intelligent, and deeply bonded to their families.
breeds.care_notes: Needs regular brushing for semi-long coat. Vocal but less extreme than Siamese. Needs social engagement.

breeds.name: Bombay
breeds.description: Created to resemble a miniature black panther. Bombay cats are social, affectionate, and surprisingly dog-like in their people-orientation.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Prone to craniofacial defects — check breeder carefully. Very social — benefits from feline company.

breeds.name: Japanese Bobtail
breeds.description: Good luck cats with distinctive pom-pom tails. Japanese Bobtails are the model for the famous Maneki-neko lucky cat figurines.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Active and vocal. Bonds strongly with family. Excellent with children.

breeds.name: Turkish Van
breeds.description: The swimming cat. Turkish Vans love water, fetch, and high places — active, intelligent cats who are far more dog-like than most breeds.
breeds.care_notes: Minimal grooming despite semi-long coat. Loves water. Needs vertical space and active play. Independent.

breeds.name: Somali
breeds.description: Long-haired Abyssinians. Somalis are strikingly beautiful, endlessly curious, and need significant environmental enrichment.
breeds.care_notes: Twice-weekly brushing for longer coat. Very active — needs playtime and vertical space.

breeds.name: Selkirk Rex
breeds.description: The cat in sheep's clothing — Selkirk Rex have glorious curly coats and patient, tolerant personalities perfect for families.
breeds.care_notes: Brushing 2-3x weekly — avoid over-grooming to preserve curls. Very tolerant. Good with children.

breeds.name: Ocicat
breeds.description: Wild-looking but completely domestic. Ocicats resemble wild cats but are entirely domestic — social, active, and surprisingly trainable.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Highly trainable — can learn leash walking. Needs active play. Very social.

breeds.name: American Curl
breeds.description: Named for their uniquely curled-back ears. American Curls are gentle, interactive cats who remain kitten-like well into adulthood.
breeds.care_notes: Regular ear cleaning due to unique shape. Gentle but playful. Adapts well to most households.

breeds.name: LaPerm
breeds.description: Naturally curly-coated cats that developed spontaneously on an Oregon farm. LaPerms are affectionate, active, and people-oriented companions.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing despite curly coat. Easy grooming overall. Affectionate and social.

breeds.name: Pixiebob
breeds.description: Resembling a bobcat with their spotted coats and bobbed tails. Pixiebobs are devoted, dog-like cats who are wonderful family companions.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Very dog-like — can be leash trained. Loyal and loving. Adapts well.

breeds.name: Ragamuffin
breeds.description: Ragdoll cousins with more color variety. Ragamuffins are sweet, gentle giants who are remarkably patient with children and other pets.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly brushing. Prone to HCM. Very patient and gentle — excellent family cats.

breeds.name: Manx
breeds.description: Tailless island cats with a dog-like personality. Manx cats are loyal, playful, and surprisingly adept hunters.
breeds.care_notes: Regular veterinary checks for Manx syndrome (spinal issues). Active and playful. Dog-like loyalty.

breeds.name: Singapura
breeds.description: The world's smallest cat breed. Singapuras are ticked tabby cats with enormous eyes and outsized personalities — mischievous and endlessly entertaining.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Very active despite small size. Social — needs regular interaction.

breeds.name: Burmilla
breeds.description: Accidental Burmese-Chinchilla cross that became a breed in its own right. Burmillas are beautiful, gentle, and adaptable.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly brushing. Gentle and sociable. Less demanding than Burmese parent. Good family cats.

breeds.name: Chausie
breeds.description: Jungle cat hybrid. Chausies are athletic, social, and need extensive space and enrichment — stunning cats for experienced owners.
breeds.care_notes: Needs extensive space and enrichment. Very active. Not suitable for apartments. Experienced owner preferred.

breeds.name: Korat
breeds.description: Ancient Thai cats considered good luck. Korats are gentle, quiet, and form intense bonds with their people.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Very sensitive to loud noises and changes. Quiet but deeply loving.

breeds.name: Minuet (Napoleon)
breeds.description: Munchkin-Persian cross with short legs and round faces. Minuets are sweet, gentle, and wonderfully adaptable little companions.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming for longer coat variety. Short legs — avoid jumping from high surfaces.

breeds.name: Thai (Traditional Siamese)
breeds.description: The original Siamese before extreme breeding changed the look. Traditional Thais have rounder faces and a gentler, less extreme personality.
breeds.care_notes: Easier temperament than modern Siamese. Still vocal. Social and loving.

breeds.name: Havana Brown
breeds.description: Rich brown cats with vivid green eyes and a playful, social personality. Havana Browns are intelligent, loving, and genuinely engaging.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Very social — needs regular interaction. Intelligent and playful.

breeds.name: Lykoi
breeds.description: The werewolf cat. Lykois have a patchy coat that gives them a wild, Halloween-cat appearance, but are gentle, loyal companions.
breeds.care_notes: No grooming needed for patchy coat. Prone to cold — needs warm environment. Loyal and dog-like.

breeds.name: Munchkin
breeds.description: Short-legged cats who navigate the world with impressive competence. Munchkins are active, sociable, and surprisingly athletic.
breeds.care_notes: Regular health monitoring for mobility issues. Active and playful. Controversy around breed ethics.

breeds.name: Serengeti
breeds.description: Developed to resemble a serval. Serengetis are athletic, social, and long-legged — striking cats for active households.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Very active — needs space and enrichment. Social and vocal.

breeds.name: Nebelung
breeds.description: Long-haired Russian Blues with the same quiet devotion and gentle nature. Nebelungs bond deeply but warm to strangers slowly.
breeds.care_notes: Twice-weekly brushing. Shy initially — allow adjustment time. Devoted once bonded.

breeds.name: American Bobtail
breeds.description: Wild-looking bobtails with interactive personalities. American Bobtails are adaptable, intelligent, and surprisingly dog-like.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care in shorthair variety. Adapts to most lifestyles. Intelligent and playful. Good traveler.

breeds.name: Peterbald
breeds.description: Russian hairless cats with an Oriental body type. Peterbalds are intensely social and loving — they need near-constant companionship.
breeds.care_notes: Skin care needed. Cannot tolerate cold. Very social — suffers alone. Needs feline companion ideally.

breeds.name: Cymric
breeds.description: Long-haired Manx cats with the same dog-like personality and playful nature. Cymrics are loyal, gentle companions.
breeds.care_notes: Twice-weekly brushing. Spinal checks needed. Dog-like loyalty. Good family cats.

breeds.name: Khao Manee
breeds.description: Ancient Thai royal cats with pure white coats and jewel-colored eyes. Khao Manees are curious, affectionate, and somewhat rare.
breeds.care_notes: Deaf whites possible — check hearing. Active and social. Easy care coat.

breeds.name: Suphalak
breeds.description: One of the ancient Thai breeds from the Cat Book Poems. Suphalaks are gentle, sociable cats with rich copper coats.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Gentle and sociable. Rare outside Thailand.

breeds.name: Aegean
breeds.description: Natural Greek island cats. Aegeans are naturally healthy, intelligent, and social — the result of centuries of natural development.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Natural breed — very healthy. Active and social.

breeds.name: Donskoy
breeds.description: Russian hairless cats with a slightly different genetic makeup from the Sphynx. Donskoys are warm, social, and intensely loyal.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly skin bathing. Cannot tolerate cold. Very social. Dog-like devotion.

breeds.name: Highlander
breeds.description: Large cats with curled ears and optional bobbed tails. Highlanders are confident, playful, and wonderful family cats.
breeds.care_notes: Regular ear cleaning. Very dog-like. Playful and social. Adapts well to families.

breeds.name: Ojos Azules
breeds.description: Remarkable for their deep blue eyes that appear in non-colorpoint cats. Ojos Azules are gentle, quiet, and devoted.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Blue eyes from unique genetics. Rare. Gentle and devoted.

breeds.name: Holland Lop
breeds.description: One of the most popular rabbit breeds. Holland Lops are floppy-eared charmers with gentle, affectionate personalities perfect for families.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily exercise outside enclosure. Hay should be 80% of diet. Spaying/neutering recommended.

breeds.name: Mini Rex
breeds.description: Velvet-coated rabbits with distinctively dense plush fur. Mini Rex are curious, gentle, and wonderful for children.
breeds.care_notes: Plush coat needs weekly brushing. Daily exercise outside cage. Hay as primary diet.

breeds.name: Lionhead
breeds.description: Named for their distinctive mane of wool. Lionheads are playful, social, and strikingly beautiful rabbits.
breeds.care_notes: Mane requires regular brushing to prevent matting. Energetic — needs daily exercise.

breeds.name: American Guinea Pig
breeds.description: The classic smooth-coated guinea pig. Americans are gentle, sociable, and vocal — perfect first small pets.
breeds.care_notes: Social animals — keep in pairs minimum. Daily fresh vegetables. Vitamin C essential in diet.

breeds.name: Abyssinian Guinea Pig
breeds.description: Rosette-coated guinea pigs with more personality than you'd expect. Abyssinians are active, curious, and entertaining.
breeds.care_notes: Rosette coat needs regular brushing. Very active — needs space to explore.

breeds.name: Peruvian Guinea Pig
breeds.description: Long-haired guinea pigs with floor-length coats. Peruvians are gentle but require significant grooming commitment.
breeds.care_notes: Daily brushing essential to prevent matting. Regular trimming needed. Gentle handling required.

breeds.name: Budgerigar
breeds.description: The world's most popular pet bird. Budgies are small but enormously entertaining — they can learn to talk, whistle tunes, and do tricks.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily out-of-cage time. Social — pairs are happier. Fresh food daily. Avian vet recommended.

breeds.name: Cockatiel
breeds.description: Cockatiels are the perfect gateway bird — affectionate, trainable, and talented whistlers who bond deeply with their families.
breeds.care_notes: Needs daily out-of-cage flight time. Social — do well in pairs. Fresh food daily. Can develop hormonal issues.

breeds.name: Conure
breeds.description: Miniature parrots with maximum attitude. Conures are loud, playful, and intensely bonded to their people — not for noise-sensitive households.
breeds.care_notes: Needs significant daily interaction. Very loud — apartment neighbors may object. Needs toys and enrichment.

breeds.name: Lovebird
breeds.description: Lovebirds live up to their name when bonded with a mate. They are active, colorful, and can be aggressive with other birds.
breeds.care_notes: Bond most strongly when kept in pairs. Can be aggressive with other birds. Needs enrichment and space.

breeds.name: Canary
breeds.description: Bred for their song over centuries. Canaries are beautiful, musical birds that prefer to be admired rather than handled.
breeds.care_notes: Males sing most beautifully. Generally prefer not to be handled. Beautiful song fills a room.

breeds.name: Betta Fish
breeds.description: Living jewels for desktop aquariums. Bettas are intelligent fish that recognize their owners and interact with the environment.
breeds.care_notes: Cannot be housed with other male bettas. Needs heated water (76-82°F). Needs enrichment — they are smart.

breeds.name: Goldfish
breeds.description: Ancient fish with surprising longevity when properly cared for. Goldfish are peaceful, social, and endlessly calming.
breeds.care_notes: Needs proper filtration — they produce a lot of waste. Cold water fish — no heater needed. Can live 10-15 years.

breeds.name: Hamster (Syrian)
breeds.description: The quintessential first pet. Syrian hamsters are solitary by nature, coming alive at dusk for their nightly adventures.
breeds.care_notes: Must be kept alone — will fight other hamsters. Needs large wheel. Active at night.

breeds.name: Gerbil
breeds.description: Diurnal burrowing rodents that make wonderful first pets. Gerbils are active, social, and absolutely fascinating to watch.
breeds.care_notes: Social animals — keep in same-sex pairs. Needs bedding for burrowing. Active during the day.

breeds.name: Rat (Fancy)
breeds.description: The most intelligent small pet. Fancy rats are highly trainable, deeply social, and bond strongly with their owners.
breeds.care_notes: Social animals — keep in pairs minimum. Need extensive daily out-of-cage time. Can learn tricks.

breeds.name: Chinchilla
breeds.description: Incredibly soft fur and the personality to match. Chinchillas are gentle, curious, and long-lived small pets.
breeds.care_notes: Cannot get wet — dust baths only. Nocturnal — active in evenings. Very long-lived for size. Cannot tolerate heat.

breeds.name: Ferret
breeds.description: Cartoon characters brought to life. Ferrets are relentlessly playful, impossibly mischievous, and endlessly entertaining.
breeds.care_notes: Must be ferret-proofed — they get into everything. Need 4+ hours out of cage daily. Social — pairs are happier.

breeds.name: Hedgehog
breeds.description: Prickly outside, sweetly curious within. African pygmy hedgehogs are solitary, nocturnal, and charming for patient owners.
breeds.care_notes: Solitary — keep alone. Nocturnal. Handle daily to maintain tameness. Cannot tolerate cold.

breeds.name: Sugar Glider
breeds.description: Tiny marsupials that glide between trees. Sugar gliders bond intensely with their owners and need to be carried throughout the day.
breeds.care_notes: Require extensive socialization — carry in bonding pouch. Social — need companions. Special diet required.

breeds.name: Dalmador
breeds.description: Dalmatian-Labrador mix combining the Lab's friendliness with the Dalmatian's distinctive energy.
breeds.care_notes: Daily vigorous exercise. Moderate grooming. Early training recommended.

breeds.name: Goldendoodle
breeds.description: One of the most popular hybrid breeds — Golden Retriever meets Poodle for intelligence, low shedding, and an irresistible personality.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks. High energy — needs daily vigorous exercise. Excellent therapy dogs.

breeds.name: Labradoodle
breeds.description: The original Doodle. Labradoodles were developed as hypoallergenic guide dogs and became one of the most beloved family dogs.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. High energy needs. Excellent service and therapy dog candidates.

breeds.name: Cavapoo
breeds.description: Cavalier-Poodle cross that combines the best of both: the Cavalier's gentle heart with the Poodle's intelligence and low shedding.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. Prone to Cavalier heart issues — screen parents. Moderate exercise needs.

breeds.name: Cockapoo
breeds.description: One of the oldest hybrid breeds — playful, intelligent, and low-shedding. Cockapoos are wonderful all-around family companions.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming every 6-8 weeks. Moderate daily exercise. Very sociable.

breeds.name: Bernedoodle
breeds.description: Bernese Mountain Dog meets Poodle. Bernedoodles have the tri-color beauty of the Berner with the intelligence and lower shedding of the Poodle.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming. Prone to inherited conditions. Moderate daily exercise. Wonderful family companions.

breeds.name: Sheepadoodle
breeds.description: Old English Sheepdog meets Poodle. Sheepadoodles are large, fluffy, and remarkably gentle herding-intelligence hybrids.
breeds.care_notes: Professional grooming every 6-8 weeks. Needs vigorous daily exercise. Very smart — needs mental stimulation.

breeds.name: Pomsky
breeds.description: Pomeranian-Husky cross. Pomskies are strikingly beautiful with Husky looks in a smaller package — energetic and opinionated.
breeds.care_notes: Needs significant daily exercise for size. Can be stubborn. Vocal tendencies. Regular brushing.

breeds.name: Aussiedoodle
breeds.description: Australian Shepherd meets Poodle. Aussiedoodles are brilliantly intelligent, athletic, and need serious mental and physical engagement.
breeds.care_notes: Needs 2+ hours daily exercise. Professional grooming. Excels at dog sports. Very high intelligence.

breeds.name: Schnoodle
breeds.description: Schnauzer-Poodle cross. Schnoodles are alert, intelligent, and low-shedding — wonderful companions for active families.
breeds.care_notes: Regular professional grooming. Daily exercise and mental stimulation needed. Very trainable.

breeds.name: Whoodle
breeds.description: Wheaten Terrier-Poodle cross. Whoodles combine the Wheaten's joyful personality with Poodle intelligence and low shedding.
breeds.care_notes: Regular grooming. High energy — needs vigorous daily exercise. Very affectionate.

breeds.name: Sokoke
breeds.description: One of the rarest domestic breeds, originating from Kenya's Arabuko-Sokoke forest. Sokokes are athletic, communicative, and deeply bonded.
breeds.care_notes: Easy care coat. Active and needs enrichment. Very rare breed.

breeds.name: European Shorthair
breeds.description: The quintessential European domestic cat — naturally selected over centuries for health, intelligence, and adaptability.
breeds.care_notes: Very hardy breed. Easy care coat. Natural hunters. Long-lived.

breeds.name: York Chocolate
breeds.description: Beautiful chocolate and lavender-coated cats from New York. York Chocolates are playful, curious, and devoted family companions.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing for longer coat. Playful and social. Rare breed.

breeds.name: Tiffanie
breeds.description: Australian Burmilla-Chinchilla cross. Tiffanies are gentle, beautiful cats with silky coats and balanced personalities.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing for silky coat. Gentle and balanced. Rare outside Australia.

breeds.name: Aphrodite
breeds.description: One of Cyprus's two natural breed cats. Aphrodites are large, intelligent, and devoted companions with a natural island hardiness.
breeds.care_notes: Regular brushing for longer coat. Very healthy natural breed. Devoted companions.

breeds.name: Lionhead Rabbit
breeds.description: Show-stopping mane and a personality to match. Lionheads are sociable, playful, and stunning rabbits.
breeds.care_notes: Regular mane brushing. Energetic — needs daily exercise. Social — benefits from a companion.

breeds.name: Rex Rabbit
breeds.description: Velvet-coated rabbits with plush, distinctive fur. Rex Rabbits are calm, intelligent, and gentle — wonderful family pets.
breeds.care_notes: Weekly brushing. Calm temperament. Daily exercise needed.

breeds.name: African Grey Parrot
breeds.description: The most intelligent parrot species. African Greys have the cognitive ability of a 5-year-old and the emotional needs to match.
breeds.care_notes: Requires extensive daily interaction and mental stimulation. Very long-lived. Needs specialist avian vet.

breeds.name: Eclectus Parrot
breeds.description: Strikingly dimorphic parrots — males and females look completely different. Eclectus are calm, gentle, and excellent talkers.
breeds.care_notes: Dietary needs differ from other parrots — needs fresh foods. Males and females differ in personality.

breeds.name: Fancy Mouse
breeds.description: Tiny but endlessly entertaining. Fancy mice are inquisitive, social, and active — perfect observation pets.
breeds.care_notes: Social — keep in groups. Needs enrichment. Short lifespan. Males smell more than females.

breeds.name: Macaw (Blue and Gold)
breeds.description: Majestic parrots with stunning plumage and enormous personalities. Blue and Gold Macaws bond intensely with their owners.
breeds.care_notes: Needs huge cage and daily out-of-cage flight. Extremely loud. Very long-lived commitment — plan for 50+ years.

breeds.name: Cockatoo (Umbrella)
breeds.description: The neediest parrot. Umbrella Cockatoos are extraordinarily affectionate and social — but their emotional needs rival a toddler's.
breeds.care_notes: Needs hours of daily interaction. Extremely loud. Can become destructive if neglected. Not for first-time bird owners.

breeds.name: Axolotl
breeds.description: The smiling salamander that never metamorphoses. Axolotls are fascinating, docile aquatic pets with alien beauty.
breeds.care_notes: Needs cold water (60-68°F). Special diet. Cannot be housed with most fish. Increasingly rare in the wild.

breeds.name: Bearded Dragon
breeds.description: The most popular pet lizard for good reason. Bearded Dragons are gentle, curious, and genuinely interactive reptiles.
breeds.care_notes: Needs UVB lighting and proper heating gradient. Varied diet of insects and vegetables. Regular handling maintains tameness.

breeds.name: Crested Gecko
breeds.description: Rediscovered in 1994 after being thought extinct. Crested Geckos are hardy, docile, and wonderful beginner reptiles.
breeds.care_notes: Temperature-sensitive — cannot tolerate heat above 80°F. Evening and nocturnal activity. Arboreal — needs vertical space.

breeds.name: Red-Eared Slider
breeds.description: America's most popular pet turtle. Red-Eared Sliders are long-lived, fascinating aquatic animals requiring proper setup.
breeds.care_notes: Needs large aquatic setup with basking area. UVB lighting essential. Water filtration critical. Long-lived commitment.

breeds.name: Ball Python
breeds.description: The most popular pet snake. Ball Pythons are docile, manageable, and beautiful — ideal for first-time snake owners.
breeds.care_notes: Needs proper heating (88-92°F warm side). Feeding once weekly to biweekly. Hides are essential for security.

breeds.name: Clownfish
breeds.description: Made famous by Finding Nemo. Clownfish are colorful, active, and fascinating symbiotic fish for marine aquariums.
breeds.care_notes: Saltwater aquarium required. Can be kept with anemones. Territorial — limited numbers per tank.

breeds.name: Discus
breeds.description: The king of freshwater aquarium fish. Discus are stunningly beautiful but require pristine water conditions and specialist care.
breeds.care_notes: Very sensitive to water parameters. Warm water required (82-88°F). Social — keep in groups of 6+. Expert level care.

breeds.name: Leopard Gecko
breeds.description: The perfect beginner reptile. Leopard Geckos are easy to handle, long-lived, and come in hundreds of beautiful color morphs.
breeds.care_notes: Ground-dwelling — needs horizontal space. Needs warm side (88-92°F). No UVB required. Mealworm and cricket diet.

breeds.name: Corn Snake
breeds.description: The best beginner snake. Corn Snakes are hardy, manageable, beautiful, and remarkably docile with regular handling.
breeds.care_notes: Needs secure enclosure — escape artists. Temperature gradient needed. Weekly feeding. Many beautiful color morphs available.

breeds.name: Miniature Horse
breeds.description: Full-sized horse personality in a tiny package. Mini horses are social, intelligent, and can even be kept as house pets.
breeds.care_notes: Needs adequate outdoor space. Social — need companions. Special dietary needs. Regular farrier and vet care.

breeds.name: Koi Fish
breeds.description: Living jewels of the garden pond. Koi are ancient Japanese fish that recognize their owners and can live for decades.
breeds.care_notes: Needs large outdoor pond with filtration. Social — keep in groups. Can be hand-fed. Winter care needed in cold climates.

breeds.name: Blue-Tongued Skink
breeds.description: Blue tongues flash as a defense mechanism, but Blue-Tongued Skinks are among the most docile, interactive lizards available.
breeds.care_notes: Ground-dwelling lizard needs horizontal space. UVB lighting beneficial. Omnivorous — varied diet. Very handleable.
